                    <p><a href="#top3">return to top</a></p>
                <a name="t_ssh" id="t_ssh"></a>
                <h4>Do you allow telnet / SSH access?</h4>
                    <p>Unfortunately on shared accounts we are not able to allow access of that type due to security issues. On all VPS and V-Dedicated plans full SSH access is allowed.</p>
                    <p><a href="#top3">return to top</a></p>
                <a name="t_database" id="t_database"></a>
                <h4>What kind of database access do you provide?</h4>
                    <p>Our main shared hosting only allows for MySQL access, though we do have special shared servers that provide PostgreSQL and SQLite, available upon request.  We do not offer MSSQL or Microsoft Access Database.</p>
                    <p><a href="#top3">return to top</a></p>
                <a name="t_operatingsystem" id="t_operatingsystem"></a>
                <h4>What Operating System do you use on the servers?</h4>
                    <p>Our servers currently run CentOS 4.x and Redhat 9, depending on the server. Our VPS systems are powered under Virtuozzo with CentOS 4.x and Redhat 9 as well.</p>
                    <p><a href="#top3">return to top</a></p>
                <a name="t_php" id="t_php"></a>
                <h4>What version of PHP do you use?</h4>
                    <p>We currently offer PHP 5.x as a default, but we have servers that run 4.4.x that are available by request for those needing older versions.  PHP 5.3 is currently only available by request on V-Dedicated and Dedicated servers</p>
                    <p><a href="#top3">return to top</a></p>
                <a name="t_apache" id="t_apache"></a>
                <h4>What version of Apache do you use?</h4>
